commitResults.messageBody:
Perform some additional refactoring to abstract the greet function and
use switch statements to deal with input
Create Task class to better manage tasks and track task state

New features in level-4 introduce types of tasks that have common
behaviours but are still functionally diferent.

The Task class is not suited to deal with these behaviours in an
efficient manner without code duplication or messy if-else checks.

We will turn Task into an abstract class and create classes Event, Todo
and Deadline which will be concrete implementations of the Task class.

Inheritance presents a clean implementation of the needed use case and
allows for common behaviours to remain in a parent class, and the
abstract class acts as a template for all tasks while allowing unique
behaviours to be defined by the implemented class itself.

Duke does not have any error handling.

Error handling needs to be added in order to deal with user input that
does not conform to the required spec.

Adding try-catch blocks allows the chatbot to deal with incorrect user
input through the use of exceptions. A custom DukeExceptions allows us
to take care of exceptions which are within the scope of what we predict
might go wrong.

Exceptions allow us to have a standardised way of dealing with Duke
related exceptions, as opposed to if-else checks which print errors.

Update Deadline and Event classes to store a LocalDateTime instead of
String for the dates itself.
